 HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/btmalliance99801.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lendl>Lendl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Is this better?</span><br>  Posts: 455<br> <font color=#000000>(7/17/03 8:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftmalliance99801frm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://homepages.dsl.ca/~kkilgour/lendlpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   More special event nights</span><hr size=1> When we did a reaver night (july 1) I think everyone had a great time trying something different. I was thinking maybe we'd try another night like that but with a different vehicle. One I'd like to try is a Prowler night. For this we would only need a few people to cert in Prowler, the rest gunners.<br>
<br>
I'd also like us to try something I'm calling Tactical Tower Taking. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  When there's a zerg, instead of joining in the base cap, we fly around and assist in taking towers or AMSs. Just to try something different and try out some actual tactics. I have ideas on how this would work. Feel free to post you own.<br>
<br>
I don't want to schedule a specific night. I think it's better that when we have a decent amount on...ie: 10+, we just be spontaneous.<br>
<br>
 <p><image src="http://stats.planetsidegaming.com/12/400624/stats.png"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#EBEFF1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/btmalliance99801.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kaeleb>Kaeleb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beer?</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#000000>(7/18/03 8:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftmalliance99801frm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: More special event nights</span><hr size=1> The mini-prowler night we did last night was fun.  We should do this more with at least 3-4 prowlers and 3-4 reaver/mosq air cover again soon!<br>
<br>
Bier <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFF0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/btmalliance99801.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lendl>Lendl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Is this better?</span><br>  Posts: 456<br> <font color=#000000>(7/18/03 9:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftmalliance99801frm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://homepages.dsl.ca/~kkilgour/lendlpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: More special event nights</span><hr size=1> For sure!<br>
<br>
Some of the good things about last night was a) there was more than one tank and b) communication with TS helped A LOT!<br>
<br>
I've hopped into a few tanks on their way to a tower and it was impoosible to warn of danger or call out targets. Plus the drivers always charged the tower blindly driving over mines and didn't know when to retreat and repair. <br>
<br>
This is key and Kreb and Sarun did a great job last night keeping the tanks alive.<br>
<br>
I'd love to get 3-4 fully crewed tanks and a few reavers for air cover and scouting. A birds eye view could also help in shelling the base from over a hill or something. That would be cool to try. <br>
<br>
To do this we would need about 15 people on or more and at least 4 with prowler cert.<br>
<br>
Anyway, that last stand in Onatha last night was great. Good job guys!<br>
<br>
 <p><image src="http://stats.planetsidegaming.com/12/400624/stats.png"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#EBEFF1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/btmalliance99801.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kaeleb>Kaeleb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beer?</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#000000>(7/19/03 8:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftmalliance99801frm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: More special event nights</span><hr size=1> Last night (Friday) Frak, Sarun and I had a few runs in a prowler.  It was great.  Two important notes for use of prowlers:  have someone with a repair gun on board, and also carry extra boxes of the chain gun ammo.<br>
<br>
It makes for much longer runs full of killing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Bier <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFF0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/btmalliance99801.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cyphre@tmalliance99801>Cyphre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(7/20/03 1:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftmalliance99801frm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: More special event nights</span><hr size=1> And who had the best shot of the night? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Well, ok so it was a really crappy reaver pilot because he was flying so low...<br>
<br>
You know, I would say an all MAX night would be a good idea...but then we would have no way to repair and no way to hack places unless we went like half and half or more than one squad. That would be one deadly force of MAXs when you've got more than 5 or something.<br>
<br>
The tanks were nice, especially being able to use reinforced armor, and in the same league would be the liberator which has a gunner and a bomber besides the pilot...so you get 9 people, 3 of which being lib pilots, and you've got the same game plan as the tank idea but then you could drop on things and not run the risk of mines or too many spitfire turrets. Well, thats my only idea...since marauders would just be like weaker smaller tanks and that wouldn't be too bright. Maybe all lightnings! Running people over is fun... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#EBEFF1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/btmalliance99801.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lendl>Lendl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Is this better?</span><br>  Posts: 462<br> <font color=#000000>(7/20/03 2:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftmalliance99801frm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://homepages.dsl.ca/~kkilgour/lendlpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: More special event nights</span><hr size=1> Marauders would not be as tough but would be really fun. Especially in a hilly region like hossin or something. Solan actually barrel rolled one twice and kept going while we were chasing down an ams...along with another marauder and some reavers. Was a blast!<br>
<br>
Anyway, good ideas. The MAX idea would be cool if we had a few people playing repair/hacker.<br>
<br>
 <p><image src="http://stats.planetsidegaming.com/12/400624/stats.png"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFF0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/btmalliance99801.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cyphre@tmalliance99801>Cyphre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#000000>(7/20/03 1:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftmalliance99801frm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: More special event nights</span><hr size=1> Yeah, guess it would be fun to do a whole offroad thing...dunno the speed difference between the marauder and prowler. You could accomplish the MAX thing with probably a single marauder, prowler, or liberator, or just have a could reavers for scouting/air support, all the while those being the ones who can repair. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#EBEFF1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/btmalliance99801.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kirverdamson>Kirver Damson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 650<br> <font color=#000000>(7/20/03 1:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ftmalliance99801frm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: More special event nights</span><hr size=1> You can always count on me to do the repair/hacks  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/